  "prompt": "How many times has Obama met Putin?",
  "response": "Barack Obama and Vladimir Putin met in person several times during Obama\u2019s presidency from 2009 to 2017. Their notable meetings include:\n\n1. **July 2009** - First meeting at the G8 Summit in L'Aquila, Italy.\n2. **June 2010** - Bilateral talks in Toronto during the G20 Summit.\n3. **November 2011** - AOC meeting in Honolulu, Hawaii during the APEC summit.\n4. **May 2012** - Meeting at the G8 Summit in Camp David, Maryland.\n5. **September 2013** - A bilateral meeting during the G20 Summit in St. Petersburg, Russia.\n6. **June 2016** - Meeting at the G20 summit in Hangzhou, China.\n\nIn addition to these formal meetings, they interacted in various multilateral settings and through phone calls. Overall, they had approximately 6 to 8 significant face-to-face meetings during Obama's presidency, depending on how one counts informal interactions.",
